The paper proposes a new model for learning entity and relationship embeddings in knowledge graphs using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). This involves treating entities and relationships as one-dimensional numerical sequences and applying CNNs to triplets of head, relationship, and tail to get confidence scores. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers topics related to machine learning, including neural networks, which are used in the proposed model. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers topics related to the theory and applications of machine learning, which are relevant to the proposed model. 
- cs.DB (Databases): This sub-category covers topics related to database systems, including knowledge graphs, which are the focus of the proposed model. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This sub-category covers topics related to natural language processing, which is often used in conjunction with knowledge graphs. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): This sub-category covers topics related to information retrieval, which is another application area for knowledge graphs.
